This repository was structured from the p-to-q repo-template conventions: file-first
public surface, explicit repository shape, short docs map, visible artifacts, and
receipts or limitations.

Short-term notice:
- Hackathon v0 is frontend-led.
- The current prototype uses fixtures and mock observation values unless marked otherwise.
- The project does not claim to find a globally shortest prompt.

Long-term notice:
- Future model integrations must label whether they are black-box, white-box, or simulated.
- Future releases must preserve the distinction between explicit reconstruction,
  shortest found prompt, and non-leaking prompt search.
- If model internals are not available, token loss, NLL, layer scan, and attribution
  panels must not be represented as true white-box measurements.
